<br>
Let me enlighten you on something here: people play for loot. I know this is a big shock so breathe deep and sit down for a few minutes before you continue. The only way to get people to play when there's no loot in it for them is if they care about supporting the people they play with. With a random bunch of folks, there's no reason for anyone to give a flying fvck through a fruit loop rolling downhill on a gravel driveway, onto the interstate, across the median and past the naked dude running from police and flashing commuters... but I digress. For all your 'experience' you apparently haven't learned this simple basic fact. Why do you suppose this has escaped your notice when everyone else who has ever played the high end game knows it so well that to mention it would be no more than to state the obvious?<br>
<br>
Of course, if you're sending level 45-49s into a plane, you won't have to worry about loot, since you won't get any... you'll just have to worry about who you can pay to retrieve the bodies.<br>
<br>
Speaking of paying... who gets to pay for raid costs, your port stones and pearls and peridots and coffins and all the other things needed to make it happen? Who gets to decide who gets what loot? Who makes groups? Balances classes? Gets people in and out? Gives instructions? By the time you answer these questions you've already got yourself back to a guild, even if you decide, contrarily, to give it a different name.<br>
<br>
As a Certified Grassy Knoll Professional Conspiracy Theorist (tm) I can only come to the conclusion that you must have a necro stocked with coffins tucked away somewhere and are looking to go into business <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
